      "writtenOn": "2017-04-21T18:11:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Double checking my understanding here:\n\u003e We are caching the |tileShader| because it holds the |tileImage|, which will cache the actual image pixels after it generates them once.\n\nCorrect.  We could have cached the SkImage instead, but this way we avoid re-allocating the shader on each draw.\n\n\u003e The |dstColorSpace| should previously have been on the cache key, since it will affect how we generate the pixels.  I am now adding an SkColorSpace to the cache key - which might be the |dstColorSpace| or |fColorSpace|.\n\u003e The blend behavior flag is useful to describe the differences in what the color space on the cache key \"means\".\n\nSGTM.",
